        <Summary>Active Network Security Tool</Summary>
        <Description>Hping is one of the de facto tools for security auditing and testing of firewalls and networks. It handles fragmentation and arbitrary packet body and size, and can be used to transfer files under supported protocols. Using it you can test firewall rules, perform (spoofed) port scanning, test net performance using different protocols, packet size, TOS (type of service), and fragmentation, do path MTU discovery, transfer files (even between fascist firewalls), perform traceroute-like actions under different protocols, fingerprint remote OSs, audit a TCP/IP stack, etc. It is a good tool for learning.</Description>
